&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior EHR Integration Analyst serves as a senior technical resource responsible for supporting, implementing, and optimizing interoperability solutions across GeneDx&#39;s EHR integration portfolio. This role leads complex Point-to-Point, vendor, and Epic Aura integration initiatives while partnering with customers, vendors, Product, Engineering, Clinical Operations, and Implementation teams to deliver scalable, reliable integration solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior EHR Integration Analyst provides advanced technical leadership through complex troubleshooting, solution design, documentation standards, testing methodologies, and mentorship while driving continuous improvement across support, implementation, and interoperability processes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a primary support resource for EHR interoperability solutions and integration workflows.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor, triage, investigate, and coordinate resolution of customer-reported issues and integration alerts.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize Salesforce, ServiceNow, Jira, and other support tools to document, track, and manage support requests and enhancement opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead complex troubleshooting efforts and root cause analysis across Product, Engineering, Operations, vendors, and customer technical teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in shared support rotations across the EHR Integration &amp;amp; Optimization team.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and coordinate complex integration lifecycle activities across GeneDx&#39;s interoperability portfolio, including discovery, workflow analysis, requirements gathering, testing, implementation readiness, go-live support, and ongoing operational support.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead or support onboarding and implementation activities for EHR, interoperability, and vendor integration solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead workflow discovery, technical requirements gathering, integration planning, and stakeholder discussions to deliver scalable interoperability solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and execute documented testing scenarios, test scripts, and validation procedures for supported integrations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate testing activities and support release validation, regression testing, and implementation readiness efforts.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and promote standards for integration documentation, workflow diagrams, testing artifacts, support runbooks, troubleshooting guides, and implementation records.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document interface mappings, workflow decisions, message translations, dependencies, and operational considerations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Engineering, consultants, and interoperability platform resources supporting Redox, Corepoint, HL7 interfaces, APIs, and related technologies.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a technical subject matter expert for supported interoperability platforms, vendor capabilities, and integration workflows.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate ownership by proactively coordinating stakeholders, driving discussions, documenting decisions, tracking action items, and ensuring issues progress to resolution.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&g

