&lt;h3 class=&quot;heading-l&quot;&gt;A culture that plays to win, because patie

&lt;p&gt;GeneDx (Nasdaq: WGS) delivers personalized and actionable health insights to inform diagnosis, direct treatment, and improve drug discovery. The company is uniquely positioned to accelerate the use of genomic and large-scale clinical information to enable precision medicine as the standard of care. GeneDx is at the forefront of transforming healthcare through its industry-leading exome and genome testing and interpretation services, fueled by the world’s largest, rare disease data sets. For more information, please visit&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.genedx.com/&quot;&gt;www.genedx.com&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TERRITORY: Houston&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Schedule: Monday - Friday standard business hours (plus travel as needed, including some required weekends, evenings or overnights, to attend conferences or special events, etc.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities include:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Focusing within adult specialty segments, the RAE introduces and secures new business, and increases existing business, for GeneDx.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accomplishes these tasks through partnership and problem-solving with adult specialty call points in the assigned territory, through consultative selling, education, and serving as the &quot;first line&quot; of account management for physicians and their staff.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accountable for lead generation in an assigned territory, as well as physician and staff satisfaction with GeneDx programs and services, and coordination of sales/service activities among GeneDx team members.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinates with operations to ensure consistent follow up and timely issue resolutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implements agreed upon sales and marketing plans and actively supports development events such as physician dinners and special events.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospects and establishes new physicians by actively managing a physician development pipeline and clear illustration and communication of value propositions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promotes GeneDx services consultatively, determines customer needs and requirements and makes recommendations to physicians and staff of the various solutions GeneDx can offer them.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holds in-person client meetings, as well as virtual meetings. Expectation for field time is 4.5 days a week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties may be assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Qualifications include:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelors degree in Life Sciences, Biotechnology, Business, Marketing, or other related field &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Masters degree in Life Sciences, Biotechnology, or other related field a plus&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years in healthcare sales, preferably in a physician sales/services environment or 2+ years of experience as a genetic counselor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferred experience with neurology, immunology, rheumatology and/or other specialty segments in the adult setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess a keen technical aptitude and demonstrated ability to promote multiple service offerings and business opportunities at any given time&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional demeanor and communication&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;History of integrity and professional ethics&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works as a team player to provide quality patient care, whether direct or indirect&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a valid driver&#39;s license&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to handle difficult situations and interactions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work independently and successfully manage time and territory activities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
